  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Il Giardino delgi Ulivi</strong> is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner in an elegant setting. Enjoy authentic Sicilian dishes using local ingredients in the spacious dining room or on the outdoor terrace overlooking the sea.</p>
<p><strong>La Melarancia Pool Bar</strong> serves drinks and light snacks during the day.</p>
<p><strong>Lounge Bar</strong> has a wide selection of local and international drinks, as well as quiet atmosphere where you can relax before of after dinner.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pools &amp; Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>The hotel's outdoor pool boasts panoramic views and offers plenty of with sunbeds and umbrellas. It's normally open from May to September and pool towels are provided.</p>
<p>A shuttle bus is available to a local beach where sunbeds and umbrellas can be hired for approx. €25 per day.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Spa </strong></span></p>
<p>A sellness area offers massages and treatments (local charge) as well as a fitness room.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>General Facilities </strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span>Free wiwi</li>
<li>Free shuttle bus to and from Taormina centre </li>
<li>Free Parking</li>
<li>Panoramic Terrace </li>
<li>Garden</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Grand Hotel San Pietro have <strong>Family Deluxe Rooms</strong> which are located in the north wing of the hotel. These rooms overlook the Ionian Sea and are made up of two interconnecting rooms with two bathrooms and two balconies which are also interconnecting. </p>
<p> </p>]]></familyDescription>
